uk.blankaspect.common.json

Class JsonArray

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.blankaspect.common.basictree.AbstractNode
      • uk.blankaspect.common.basictree.ListNode
        • uk.blankaspect.common.json.JsonArray
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable, ITreeNode<AbstractNode>

    public class JsonArray
extends ListNode
    This class implements a JSON array. A JSON array contains zero or more elements that are JSON values. The elements may be of different types (eg, a mixture of JSON numbers and JSON strings).

    An array begins with a '[' (U+005B) and ends with a ']' (U+005D). Adjacent elements are separated with a ',' (U+002C).
